      <div class="comment_body">
        <p><strong>Dynamic IDL Compiling.</strong>  You could also use ORBit, which supports dynamic IDL compiling:</p>

<p><a href="http://www.gnome.org/projects/ORBit2/python/dynamic_idl.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.gnome.org/projects/ORBit2/python/dynamic_idl.html</a></p>

<p>This is especially useful for clients, as you don't have to compile the IDLs to stubs and skeletons beforehand.</p>

      </div>
